Description: A set of functions for analyzing the structure of forests
        based on the leaf area density (LAD) and leaf area index (LAI)
        measures calculated from Airborne Laser Scanning (ALS), i.e.,
        scanning lidar (Light Detection and Ranging) data. The
        methodology is discussed and described in Almeida et al. (2019)
        <doi:10.3390/rs11010092> and Stark et al. (2012)
        <doi:10.1111/j.1461-0248.2012.01864.x>.
